      "id": 1,
      "title": "\"Green Tadakod Initiative\": World Environment Day Tree Plantation Drive 2025🌿",
      "description": "On the occasion of World Environment Day, a comprehensive plantation drive was organized across Tadakod village. Led by the Gram Panchayat President and local volunteers, the event focused on planting shade-giving and fruit-bearing trees in public spaces and along main roads. Participants engaged in a community dialogue about sustainable living and the long-term benefits of a healthy ecosystem. The enthusiastic involvement of local youth and elders successfully reinforced the village's commitment to a cleaner, greener future.📝",
      "date": "2025-06-05",
      "location": "Tadakod Village, Dharwad District, Karnataka📍",
      "objective": "To celebrate World Environment Day by enhancing the local green cover and educating the community on the vital importance of environmental conservation.🎯",
      "total_beneficiaries": "Approximately 600+ residents of Tadakod village and the surrounding community.👥",
      "supporting_organization": "Chief Guest: Smt. Doddavva Karikatti (President, Gram Panchayat, Tadakod)\r\nOrganized By: Tadakod Gram Panchayat in collaboration with local community volunteers.🤝",
